In blog post, I'm going break down toxic aspects Apple Watch activity tracking three broad categories. I'll show countering example different software succeeds Apple's Activity app fails. I'll let know plan 2022.

Let's dive in.

## Tracking Things Bad, Actually

What underpins Apple Watch activity tracking feature idea Apple Watch constantly track activity accurately _and_ tracking activity _per se_ good idea. disagree points. Let's examine counterexamples.

The Apple Watch wants standing moving around least one minute per hour, twelve hours per day. Seems reasonable, right? work desk day, having someone remind move around periodically good idea.

Another problem watch measures "exercise" based heart rate. Different people will different criteria heart rate constitutes "exercise", so Apple Watch uses algorithms establish individual baseline measure from. algorithm opaque ‚Äì no visibility influence works.

I go 30-minute walk spouse, we'll wear Apple Watches. We'll start "outdoor walk" exercise watches. when we're done, she'll 30 minutes exercise I'll two. really frustrating.

Let's go further.

The idea Apple Watch accurately track activity misleading. Its sensors limited.

- watch measure distance travelled running activity using GPS, when ran first ever race, 5km long, reported 4.2km distance travelled.
- heart rate sensor not accurate ‚Äì I've seen report heart rates below resting rate above max rate.
- "stories climbed stairs" measurement, based its barometer, not accurate. I've seen Watch credit 20 stories during elevator trip, I've seen fail credit stories when running down stairs home.

These measurements slightly flawed, flaws compound when measurements combined together estimate even complicated metrics. Let's stride length example.

The Apple Watch combine distance travelled (via GPS) accelerometer measurements arm swing calculate average stride length. GPS isn't accurate, saw earlier, stride length calculated will inaccurate.

Stride length one example; Apple keeps track "measurements" one. university algorithms class, learned important lesson: garbage in, garbage out. can't build algorithm gives accurate output inaccurate input.

Let's look complicated example: cardiovascular health.

Apple algorithm combines set inputs (heart rate motion sensors) estimate [V02 Max](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VO2_max), measure cardiovascular fitness. bigger number better indicates oxygen body able move lungs muscles. I've seen V02 Max estimates Apple vary wildly me.

When covid hit started wearing mask outdoors New York, V02 Max took plunge. Makes sense, right? mask reduced amount oxygen breathing. when moved home Canada, its icy sidewalks, V02 Max took hit. makes sense: need move slower, carefully, so higher heart rate slower walking pace.

The text iOS makes data seem lot authoritative is, saw garbage-in-garbage-out problem earlier. I've resent Activity Health apps accurate valid seem think data is.



![Screenshot VO2 Max Apple's Health app, describes measurement reads "VO2 max validated users 20 older."](./vo2_max.png)



The problem no user input algorithms all. can't tell Apple Watch "hey I'm wearing mask, so don't estimate V02 Max exercise." Lack user input larger problem Apple Watch Activity tracking. no users tell watch "I'm home sick today" stop pestering user throughout day close rings.

In fact, Apple Watch won't ever _not_ tell close rings. crucial mistake active, getting fit specifically, _require_ rest. weight-lifting gym isn't makes muscles grow, rather _rest_ next day makes stronger. need rest form stretching, walking, cross-training.

The Apple Watch will tell "hey, you've pushed yourself really hard, time break." Apple Watch will tell "you've standing twenty hours straight, time break." Apple Watch will ever push harder.

Trends probably worst feature Apple's Activity app combine problems we've already talked about: imperfect measurements, algorithms synthesize data bad measurements, total lack user input.

## Counter-example: Strava

The problems Apple Watch summarized follows:
